title: Gibson SG
description: The Gibson SG Standard boasts classic looks and a full set of features associated with the desirable late-'60s style SG models. With a rounded-profile mahogany neck; bound, 22-fret rosewood fingerboard; stable, long-tenon, 19th-fret neck joint and a solid mahogany body it delivers that iconic rock tone with singing sustain. The 490R and 490T Alnico II pickups provide the power to drive your amp to new heights, and a black, 5-ply, full-face pickguard put this versatile classic in a category all its own.

title: Gibson Les Paul
description: The Gibson Les Paul Traditional PRO V, commonly referred to as the “Trad PRO V.” brings Gibson tradition together with a unique feature set. Designed to make a must-have instrument for players who desire that classic Les Paul vibe, the guitar is also loaded with modern features that enhance tone and playability.

title: Gibson ES-335 Semi-Hollow
description: The Gibson ES-335 figured semi-hollow electric guitar is the perfect blend of form and function. Crafted with a thermally engineered maple centerblock, and thermally engineered quarter-sawn Adirondack spruce bracing, players will be impressed by the lightweight feel and expanded range of tonal capabilities. The AAA figured maple top is set off by a staggering gloss finish. Equipped with high-end appointments like Gibson’s hand-wired control assembly with orange drop capacitors, the new Calibrated T-Type humbucking pickups, Vintage Deluxe style tuners and lightweight Aluminum ABR-1 bridge and stopbar tailpiece anchored with steel thumb-wheels and studs, the ES-335 Figured has a refined look, feel and sound.

title: Gibson Flying V
description: From its introduction in 1958 to the present, the Gibson Flying V has remained an icon of style, in demand by players who want classic sounds and a distinctive look. This version flies with the best of them. Boasting an all mahogany body and neck, rosewood fingerboard and loaded with tone-packed BurstBucker pickups, it delivers a full range of tone and power. It's a design that will always look modern, and always turn heads. Includes hard case.

title: Fender Stratocaster
description: Since its debut in 1954, the Stratocaster has undergone constant refinement to meet the needs and desires of the working guitarist. The American Professional II Strat may be one of the most complete evolutions of this time-tested, player-proven guitar yet.

title: Fender Telecaster
description: The Limited-Edition Player Telecaster Plus Top is a great entry into the world of Fender—especially for new players—but its build quality and playability make it perfect for gigging pros, too. Sporting a gloss-finished AA flame maple top, this Tele is a real looker and equally outstanding when it comes to sound: dual Player Series single coils prove that the Plus Top can fit into any musical style with classic Fender tone.

title: Fender Jazzmaster
description: The Fender American Ultra Jazzmaster electric guitar features a maple “Modern D” neck bolted onto an alder or ash body in the iconic Jazzmaster shape, made famous by jazz legends and surf rockers alike. The rosewood fingerboard sports rolled edges for hours of playing comfort, and the tapered neck heel allows easy access to the highest register. A speedy 10”-14” compound-radius fingerboard with 22 medium-jumbo frets means effortless and accurate soloing, while two proprietary vintage Ultra Noiseless pickups and advanced controls (master volume and tone, 3-way switching) provide endless tonal possibilities – without hum. This model also includes a Fender tremolo bridge for classic whammy action, plus locking tuning machines to keep your sound precise. Chrome hardware will have you looking as good as you sound.

title: Fender Jaguar
description: Get vintage style looks and tone with Fender's Vintera '60s Jaguar. With meticulously re-created Jaguar single-coil pickups, complete with the original's focusing cages, that summon the sound and responsiveness of the guitar so many surf, punk, alt-rock and other creative guitarists fell in love with, this instrument is truly a classic reborn. The short, 24in scale length makes for easy playing and the vintage-style floating locking tremolo tailpiece remains one of Fender's most inspired developments. With the classic lead/rhythm circuit, separate rhythm volume and tone controls and the classic strangle switch, you'll discover new sonic frontiers. Includes deluxe gig bag.

title: ESP LTD EC-1000FM
description: Developed by ESP with working professionals in mind, the guitars in the LTD EC-1000 series come fully loaded with the tone and feel players need, along with the looks and quality they want. With a fast, set-through 24.75in-scale neck and smooth ebony fretboard, this EC-1000FM also features Seymour Duncan humbuckers to complement a gorgeous, flamed maple top and bound top, neck and matching headstock. As great to look at as it as to play, this instrument is versatile enough to cover multiple genres from hard rock and metal to pop and fusion jazz.

title: Ibanez S61AL Axion Label
description: Axion Label was made for metal, but offers even more for the adventurous players out there. The Axion Label models feature forward-looking developments in sound, playability and looks that take performances higher, deeper and heavier. Arm yourself with the Axion Label and get ready to break some new ground.

title: Ibanez RGA61AL Axion Label
description: Ibanez' Axion Label was made for metal, but offers even more for the adventurous players out there. The Axion Label models feature forward-looking developments in sound, playability and looks that take performances higher, deeper and heavier. Arm yourself with the Axion Label and get ready to break some new ground.

title: Ibanez RGIR9FME Iron Label 9-String
description: The RGIR9FME features a 28” scale-length which unlocks a plethora of down-tuning possibilities. The RGIR9FME’s Indian rosewood fretboard and jumbo frets offer effortless fingering up and down the full length of the fretboard. The legendary super-thin, ultra-playable Nitro Wizard neck enhances playing agility and optimizes clarity. The EMG 909 pickups offer plenty of sonic diversity and power. Designed for stability and sustain, the rock-solid Gibraltar Standard II-9 bridge is ready to handle the most extreme string bends and aggressive rhythm techniques. With the purposefully spartan “Made-for-Metal” Iron Label guitars, you won’t find a feature that doesn’t contribute directly to waking the dead.

title: Rickenbacker 360/12C63 C Series 12-String
description: It's precisely the same great-playing and sounding guitar that George Harrison made so famous, complete with double-bound body, trapeze tailpiece and unique Rickenbacker 12-string headstock. This is the guitar that provided the soundtrack to some of the most memorable music of the '60s and beyond. It matches the 1963 version in every detail with the full sound we all love. Includes hardshell case.

title: Rickenbacker 330
description: Its unique hollowbody construction, slim neck, and all-around contoured body make Rickenbacker 330 Electric Guitar so comfortable and so easy to play that it has held its status as one of the great guitars over decades. Its body is carved from a single piece of maple and precision-fitted with a solid back. The maple and rosewood neck features dual truss rods and a rosewood fingerboard with dot markers. Single-coil pickups deliver an output range from clear, ringing tone to saturated overdrive. Includes case.

title: Gretsch Guitars G6659TFM
description: Gretsch’s time-honored “Broadkaster” name now adorns the flagship guitars of its center block lineup, crafted for full-spectrum sound at high volume with powerful new pickups and a chambered spruce center block that enhances body resonance for more organic tone and comfortably lighter weight.

title: Gretsch Guitars G6659TG
description: The flagship guitar in Gretsch's center block lineup, this Broadkaster is the latest to take a name dating back to the 1940's and brings it to the modern age. Designed to deliver full-spectrum sound at high volume without undue feedback, but still maintaining body resonance for a full, organically rich tone, it brings classic looks to a modern rock-and-roll machine. Loaded with U.S.-made Full'Tron pickups to deliver serious growl while maintaining traditional Gretsch chime and brilliance, this Player's Edition Broadkaster also features a thru-strung Bigsby vibrato tailpiece to put a little wiggle in your swagger.

title: Gretsch Guitars G6128T-59
description: Inspired by the pivotal and prolific years of Gretsch’s 1950s and early ’60s golden age, Vintage Select Edition guitars are designed for the player who appreciates the finest in musical instrument heritage. The new G6128T-59 Vintage Select ’59 Duo Jet with Bigsby rocks that legacy to perfection.

title: PRS S2 Mira
description: Its all-mahogany body and asymmetrical, beveled top give the S2 Mira much of its explosive tone. And while not a super high output guitar, the S2 Mira can be overdriven into well-rounded, organic rock tones without sacrificing the punch or clarity found in higher-output guitars (or even active pickups). The bridge pickup is rich with some sparkle and substantial but tight low end, while the neck pickup is a little darker providing great balance and vintage tones. Includes gig bag.

title: PRS SE Custom 22
description: The PRS SE Custom 22 adds a more vintage tone and feel to the traditional Custom platform. This guitar has a pronounced mid-range and clarity that provides a sweet, full tonal base, allowing it to easily sit in the mix of your band or recording.

title: PRS S2 Custom 22 Semi-Hollow
description: The S2 Custom 22 is a classic workhorse guitar. Known for its exceptional clarity and warm midrange, the S2 Custom 22 Semi-Hollow has been updated here with a semi-hollow single f-hole mahogany/maple body, giving this vintage-inspired guitar a classic look and outstanding resonance. Appointments include the PRS patented molded tremolo, 85/15 S treble and bass pickups, and a push/pull coil tap on the tone control for versatile, alive vintage tone.

title: PRS SE Hollowbody Standard
description: The PRS SE Hollowbody Standard has musical midrange and outstanding resonance. The semi-hollow body provides an airy, sweet tone but with a twist of the tone knob, the dual humbuckers can get plenty of bright spank.
